.TH TL 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tl \- print the last N lines of a file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tl
.RI [ \-n
.IR count ]
.IR file ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tl
prints the last
.I count
lines of each
.IR file .
The default is 10 lines.
If no file is given, standard input is read.
Multiple files are separated by a header line.
.PP
Implemented with a circular ring buffer so memory usage is O(N) regardless
of file size.
This is the JLC equivalent of
.BR tail (1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-n " count"
Number of lines to print (default: 10).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments or invalid count.
.TP
.B 2
Cannot open a file.
.TP
.B 3
Memory allocation failure.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Print the last 10 lines of a file:
.EX
tl /var/log/syslog
.EE
.TP
Print the last 20 lines:
.EX
tl -n 20 app.log
.EE
.TP
Follow from stdin:
.EX
dmesg | tl -n 5
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tail (1),
.BR hd (1),
.BR cnt (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
